President Obama has proclaimed November 18-24, 2012, as National Family Week. In his proclamation, he emphasizes the importance of strong families in guiding the country's progress and supporting one another. The President highlights various initiatives his administration has undertaken to support families, including education, healthcare, workplace flexibility, and support for military families. He also emphasizes the need to strengthen the economy and widen opportunities for all families. The proclamation calls on states, communities, and individuals to observe the week with appropriate ceremonies and activities to honor families.